        <figure id="f07010113" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/N0020084.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"
                     scalefitheight="392px"/>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Case</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Manual control lever-to-case roll pin</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Shift retaining pin</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Manual control lever assembly</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Manual control lever seal</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil pan drain plug</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil pan-to-case bolt (20 required)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Transmission oil pan assembly</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Transmission oil pan gasket</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Transmission oil filter and seal assembly</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Transmission oil filter seal</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Raise and support the vehicle with the transmission in NEUTRAL. For additional information,
                refer to
                <exhotlnk document="../S10/S10019.htm" bookname="S10019">Jacking and Lifting in S10019</exhotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect the shift cable.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010114" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/N0020663.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Remove the cotter pin from the shift cable end.</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Remove the 2 bolts from the shift cable bracket and position it aside.
                </callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the transmission fluid pan, gasket and filter. For additional information, refer to
                Fluid Pan, Gasket and Filter in this section.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The pin should be driven up through the manual lever.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove and discard the manual valve detent lever shaft retaining pin.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010115" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0055975.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using the special tool, remove the manual valve detent lever shaft retaining pin.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010116" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/N0018716.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Be careful not to damage the manual control lever bore.</para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the manual control lever shaft assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010117" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0055976.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using a suitable tool, remove the manual control lever seal and discard.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010118" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/N0018745.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
